Measured by Honeywell Durafet pH probes every minute and recorded as an average every five minutes. These data serve as a real-time coarse monitoring/diagnostics tool of the mesocosms carbonate chemistry conditions and as time-series reflecting stability or dynamic patterns of experimental treatments. The uncertainty and drift associated with these sensors in this setting, however, prevents the use of these data beyond these uses. The most accurate and precise data source capturing the carbonate chemistry in the tanks are discrete carbonate chemistry samples analyzed for TCO2/pCO2 in the Burke-o-lator (BoL) as seen below.
